National Assembly speaker Thandi Modise's animal cruelty court case has been postponed. eNCA reporter Manqoba Mchunu explains. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The animal cruelty case against National Assembly Speaker Thandi Modise has been postponed to April next year. Modise was charged after the NSPCA reported neglected animals at her North West farm in 2014. READ: SA wildlife breeders rattled by new animal cruelty guidelines Over 50 animals were found dead with many others dehydrated and without food. AfriForum's Advocate Gerrie Nel is privately prosecuting Modise on behalf of the NSPCA. The speaker has pleaded not guilty to the charges.